      "lesson title": "AI in Clinical Trials: Bias and Validity",
      "order": 1,
      "Description": "Artificial intelligence is increasingly being used across all stages of clinical trials, from identifying suitable patients to analysing results and preparing reports. However, these tools can introduce or amplify bias in ways that are not always obvious, potentially affecting the reliability and validity of trial outcomes. This lesson explores the key risks associated with AI-driven patient selection, data analysis, and reporting, using clear, practical examples to illustrate how bias can emerge at each stage. You will learn how to recognise common warning signs and understand why human oversight remains essential when AI is involved in research. No prior technical knowledge is required, making this lesson accessible to anyone working in or around clinical research who wants to use AI more responsibly.",
