          "slidecontent": "• AI recruitment tools trained on historical data often exclude underrepresented groups by default\n• Skewed training data leads to skewed trial populations\n• Certain demographics (older adults, ethnic minorities, women) are frequently filtered out by algorithmic criteria\n• This narrows who benefits from new treatments\n• Automated eligibility screening can embed existing clinical biases without anyone noticing\n• The result is trial findings that may not apply to the broader patient population"
